Committee of the Susan G. Komen Greater Nashville Chapter, the Lutheran Women's
Missionary League, and the Full Circle Healthy Community Coalition as secretary; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Keys-Wade was a woman of abiding faith, accepting her Lord and
Savior Jesus Christ early in life and proudly serving as a member and volunteer at Mount Zion
Baptist Church; and
WHEREAS, a beloved daughter, sister, spouse, mother, and friend, Sondra Keys-Wade
was wholly devoted to her family and always endeavored to remain true to family values of the
highest order; and
WHEREAS, she will be mourned but fondly remembered by her husband, Dr. Frank D.
Wade; her bonus daughter, Katherine Josephine Wade; her brother, David Lee (Justin) Keys,
Jr.; her niece, Kaley J. Brown; her nephew, Bryson M. Coffer; her stepmother, Cheryl Keys; her
aunts, Janet M. (Timothy) Evans, Denise K. (Calvin) Johnson, Demetrice K. Rufus, and Gail M.
Taylor; her uncles, Larry McKissick and Dandridge Keys; her great-uncle, Clarence Jordan; and
a host of cousins, family, and friends; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her parents, she was preceded in death by her sister, Jana
Marie Keys; and
WHEREAS, Sondra Keys-Wade leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and
probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all
her chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we honor the life and legacy of this beautiful, on the inside
and out, kind, caring, selfless, graceful, thoughtful, fierce, brilliant, hilarious, and faith-filled
human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Sondra Denise Keys-
